resources.name: Detailed information on public opinion website

description:
The results of this second EB/EP dedicated specifically to the 2009 European Elections should be read bearing in mind that the survey was conducted at the height of the economic and financial crisis during the months of October and November 2008.
Main findings
- In the context of an economic crisis, Europeans want to put economic growth, unemployment and inflation forward as the
themes that should be the center of the 2009 campaign
- Their knowledge of the date of the European elections is improving, but the interest is slightly decreasing
- More than half of Europeans want the building of Europe process to be pursued
- The Parliament is the European institution that Europeans trust the most
Nota Bene : the analyse of the results must take into account the fact that the survey has been conducted in the middle of the economic and financial crisis (Oct. and Nov.)

#####The results by volumes are distributed as follows:
* Volume A: Countries
* Volume AA: Groups of countries
* Volume A' (AP): Trends
* Volume AA' (AAP): Trends of groups of countries
* Volume B: EU/socio-demographics
* Volume C: Country/socio-demographics
title: Special Eurobarometer 303: The 2009 European elections : expectations of the Europeans
